Nick Kyrgios withdrew from the Italian Open in Rome on Tuesday with a hip injury, casting doubt over his participation in next week&#8217;s French Open, local media reported.Kyrgios was due to play Spain&#8217;s Roberto Bautista Agut in the first round in Rome, but was replaced by lucky loser Alexandr Dolgopolov in the men&#8217;s draw.Kyrgios, who won two matches at last week&#8217;s Madrid Open before losing to eventual champion Rafael Nadal, needed treatment for a hip complaint during his first-round win over Marcos Baghdatis in Spain.-Reuters